==English==

===Etymology===
Greek ''[[suntaxis]]'', from ''[[sun-]]'' 'together' + ''[[tassein]]'' 'arrange'.

===Pronunciation===
* (''UK'') {{IPA|/ˈsɪntæks/}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|-}}

# A set of rules that govern how words are combined to form [[phrase]]s and [[sentence]]s.
# {{computer}} The formal rules of formulating the [[statements]] of a computer language
# {{linguistics}} The study of the structure of phrases, sentences and language.

